# Fixture FM5-invalid: Raw newline inside short string literal is a parse error.
#
# Hypothesis: An implementation that shares a lexer code path between short
# and long strings may accept this input. Conformant parsers MUST reject it
# because STRING_LITERAL_QUOTE forbids literal newlines.
#
# Expected: parse FAILS (Diagnostics { fatal: true }).
# Divergence signal: AcceptRejectSplit — a lenient parser accepts, a strict
# parser rejects. The presence of divergence IS the signal here.
#
# Spec: Turtle §6.3 STRING_LITERAL_QUOTE ::= '"' ([^#x22#x5C#xA#xD] | ECHAR | UCHAR)* '"'
# U+000A (#xA) is explicitly excluded from the short-string character set.
#
# NOTE: This file intentionally contains a raw newline inside double-quotes.
# Do not "fix" the file — the malformedness is the test.

<http://example/s> <http://example/p> "line1
line2" .
